HEADWORD: Capability
<hw>Ca`pa*bil"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Capabilities</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality
of being capable; capacity; capableness; esp. intellectual power or
ability.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>capability</qex> to take a thousand views of a subject.</q>
<rj><qau>H. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Capacity of being used or improved.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Capable</ent>⟦br⟧
